Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘['bɔ:rɔn]
*danh từ
 ■(hoá học) Bo

Anh - Anh
boron
['bɔ:rɒn]
■ noun the chemical element of atomic number 5, a non-metal which can be isolated as a brown, amorphous powder or (if pure) a black crystalline semiconductor. (Symbol: B)
Origin
C19: from borax, on the pattern of carbon (which it resembles).
